Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities for Binary Mixtures of Ethyl Lactate with Methacrylic Acid, Benzyl Methacrylate, and 2-Hydroxyethyl Methacrylate at (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities at (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K are presented as a function of mixture composition for the binary mixtures of ethyl lactate with methacrylic acid, benzyl methacrylate, and 2-hydroxyethyl methacrylate. From the experimental data, the excess molar volumes V E and viscosity deviations ae have been calculated. These results have been correlated with the Redlich-Kister type polynomial to derive the coefficients and standard deviation o. McAllister s three-body and four-body interaction models were also used to correlate the kinematic viscosities. These model s parameters were treated to be temperature dependent.
